not an easy listen i have found that there are two types of r & amp ; h works . there are the lively and upbeat scores , like cinderella and sound of music . then there are the slower and denser scores , like carousel and the king and i , which are not bad , but not to my liking . there are not many songs on here that appeal to the popular tastes . music theorists will probably love it . i have found that the best r and h works are the ones that sound like they were written today , most notably sound of music